body:
Both `rankdata` and `nanrankdata` call `PyArray_ArgSort` and `PyArray_EMPTY` in sequence without checking either for NULL. If either allocation fails, the result is passed to `init_iter3` which immediately dereferences it via `PyArray_STRIDES()` — segfault. If `PyArray_ArgSort` succeeds but `PyArray_EMPTY` fails, `z` also leaks.

**File(s):** `nonreduce_axis_template.c:204-209` (rankdata), `nonreduce_axis_template.c:266-271` (nanrankdata)

**Suggested fix:**

```c
// Before:
PyObject *z = PyArray_ArgSort(a, axis, NPY_QUICKSORT);
PyObject *y = PyArray_EMPTY(PyArray_NDIM(a), PyArray_SHAPE(a), NPY_DTYPE1, 0);
iter3 it;
init_iter3(&it, a, y, z, axis);

// After:
PyObject *z = PyArray_ArgSort(a, axis, NPY_QUICKSORT);
if (z == NULL) return NULL;
PyObject *y = PyArray_EMPTY(PyArray_NDIM(a), PyArray_SHAPE(a), NPY_DTYPE1, 0);
if (y == NULL) {
    Py_DECREF(z);
    return NULL;
}
iter3 it;
init_iter3(&it, a, y, z, axis);
```

See #518 for the complete report.

Found using [cext-review-toolkit](https://github.com/devdanzin/cext-review-toolkit).
